Structs/PillarboxConfiguration.html.name: PillarboxConfiguration
Structs/PillarboxConfiguration.html.abstract: This struct poses as a configuration bag for all of Pillarbox’ configurable parameters.

Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html#/s:9Pi.name: fifo
Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html#/s:9Pi.abstract: When using the first in first out strategy, items are popped from the end of the queue.

Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html#/s:9Pi.name: lifo
Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html#/s:9Pi.abstract: When using the last in first out strategy, items are popped from the start of the queue.

Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html.name: PillarboxQueueStrategy
Enums/PillarboxQueueStrategy.html.abstract: The queuing strategy to use when peeking and popping items off the queue.

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.name: init(name:url:configuration:)
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.abstract: Initializes and returns a newly allocated Pillarbox.

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.name: peek()
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.abstract: Retrieves, but does not remove, the head of the queue, or returns nil

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC3.name: pop()
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC3.abstract: Retrieves and removes the head of the queue, or returns nil

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.name: push(_:)
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC4.abstract: Pushes the specified element into the queue and persist it on the disk.

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC7.name: isEmpty
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC7.abstract: A Boolean value indicating whether the queue is empty.

Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC5.name: count
Classes/Pillarbox.html#/s:9PillarboxAAC5.abstract: The number of elements in the queue.

Classes/Pillarbox.html.name: Pillarbox
Classes/Pillarbox.html.abstract: A object-based queue which is persisted to the disk. Supports both FIFO and LIFO strategies. Should be thread-safe as well.
